  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 395°F/ Gas 6</p><p>Peel the <strong>butternut squash</strong> and cut in half using a sharp knife</p><p>Tip: Drizzle the knife with a little <strong>vegetable oil</strong> for easier chopping</p><p>Scoop out the seeds with a spoon and discard</p><p>Slice finely into half-moons</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1586950060193-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1586950060193-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1586950060193-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1586950060193-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1586950060193-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced butternut squash</strong> to a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>ground coriander</strong> to the squash with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1586950064939-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1586950064939-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1586950064939-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1586950064939-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1586950064939-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>onion wedges</strong> and<strong> sausages</strong> to the tray, spreading them out evenly</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until everything's cooked through and tender</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1586950071001-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1586950071001-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1586950071001-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1586950071001-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1586950071001-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, rinse the <strong>quinoa</strong> under<strong> cold running water</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>quinoa</strong> to a pot with a matching lid with 250ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to low and cook, covered, for 18-20 min or until all the water has absorbed and the quinoa is tender</p><p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and leave to steam-dry, uncovered, until serving</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1586950075873-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1586950075873-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1586950075873-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1586950075873-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1586950075873-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst the quinoa is cooking, slice the<strong> spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> finely on the diagonal</p><p>Chop the <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks (reserve some leaves for garnish)</p><p>Combine the <strong>onion marmalade</strong>,<strong> cider vinegar</strong> and 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp] </span><strong>olive oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> – this is your <strong>onion marmalade dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1586950080680-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1586950080680-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
